2.3 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takano &amp; Gao &amp; Hu &amp; Li &amp; Yafuso &amp; Suwito &amp; Repin &amp; Pungga &amp; Meleng &amp; Kaliang &amp; Chong &amp; Toda" authorityYear="2021" box="[195,497,798,825]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Colocasiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabahana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[195,497,798,825]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Colocasiomyia sabahana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex, new
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,870,1941]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,870,896]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Cibarial, posterior sensilla absent (ch.6-1; 
<figureCitation box="[771,862,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,798,822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[151,1435,181,774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Characters 5 and 6 on the cibarium (dorsal view) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. cristata de Meijere (B) and C. sarawakana sp. nov. (C). Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensillum; s c, sensilla campaniformia. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766410/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Phallal sheath gently curved dorsad and slightly projected triangularly at dorsobasal corner in lateral view (ch.40-2, 41-1; 
<figureCitation box="[974,1071,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 11F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1083,1125,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">24I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,870,1941]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,942,969]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Shared characters.</emphasis>
Supracervical setae approximately 4 per side, distally more or less curved, longer than inner occipital setae. Anterior reclinate orbital seta small, situated behind proclinate orbital seta; additional, interfrontal setulae on fronto-orbital plate present (ch.2-0). Eye with stout, dense interfacetal setulae (ch.3-1). Distance between antennal sockets wider than half of socket width (ch.4-0). Cibarial, medial sensilla 3–4 per side, in parallel rows narrower than sensilla campaniformia (ch.5-2; 
<figureCitation box="[676,764,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[151,250,798,822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,773]" captionTargetId="figure-22@10.[151,1435,181,774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Characters 5 and 6 on the cibarium (dorsal view) of Colocasiomyia xenalocasiae (Okada) (A), C. cristata de Meijere (B) and C. sarawakana sp. nov. (C). Abbreviations: a s, anterior sensilla; m s, medial sensilla; p s, posterior sensillum; s c, sensilla campaniformia. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766410/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Anterior dorsocentral setae behind transverse suture (ch.7- 0). Prescutellar acrostichal setae absent (ch.8-1); acrostichal setulae in 4 rows (ch.9-0). Katepisternal setae small, shorter than postpronotal setae (ch.10-1). Apical scutellar setae nearer to each other than to basal scutellar seta. Costal setae in middle row all weak, trichoid (ch.12-2). Patch covered with only minute pubescence absent on anterodorsal portion of fore tarsomere I (ch.13-1). Male abdominal sternites III–V wider than long (ch.16,17,18-0); V medially concaved on posterior margin. Female abdominal sternite III as long as wide (ch.19-0); V longer than wide (ch.21-1). Male abdominal sternite VI not pubescent at least partly, with a pair of divergent processes longer than 
<quantity box="[210,301,1339,1365]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
, widely separated from each other, bearing prominent seta on apex and small setae on submedial to distal portion (ch.23,25-0, 24,26,27-1; 
<figureCitation box="[624,744,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1780,1804]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[151,1435,181,1757]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male abdominal sternite VIs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (B in anteroventral view, C in lateral view), C. stamenicola (Carson &amp; Okada) (D in anterior view) and all species of the C. cristata subgroup (A in ventral view, E‒R in anterior view): A, C. ecornuta sp. nov.; E, C. grandis sp. nov.; F, C. vieti sp. nov.; G, C. cristata de Meijere; H, C. matthewsi sp. nov.; I, C. sulawesiana Okada &amp; Yafuso; J, C. kinabaluana sp. nov.; K, C. kotana sp. nov.; L, C. sabahana sp. nov.; M, C. sarawakana sp. nov.; N, C. pistilicola (Carson &amp; Okada); O, C. xenalocasiae (Okada); P, C. diconica (Toda &amp; Okada); Q, C. sumatrana sp. nov.; and R, C. leucocasiae sp. nov. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766420" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766420/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 9L,M</figureCitation>
). Epandrium pubescent except for anterior to ventral margin and anteroventral elongation; setae on posteroventral portion as thick as cercal setae (ch.32-0); phragma small (narrower than epandrial anteroventral corner) expansion on antero-subapical margin (ch.33-2). Surstylus vestigial, very narrow process, apically with 1 or 2 tiny, trichoid seta(e) (ch.34,35-1). Cercus pubescent only on dorsal half; ventral/apical portion more or less differentiated from upper portion, with many small setae (ch.38-0). Phallal sheath not pubescent, as thick as wide, apically not bilobed (ch.42-0, 43,44-1; 
<figureCitation box="[1056,1184,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 11F,G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1198,1256,1555,1581]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">24I,J</figureCitation>
); phallapodeme sclerotized plate directed nearly along or slightly oblique to phallal axis (ch.45-1, 46-0; 
<figureCitation box="[1126,1223,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 11F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1235,1276,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">24I</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites long, narrow slips (
<figureCitation box="[365,463,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetId="figure-43@16.[151,1435,237,1292]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Characters 40‒47 on the phallic organs of Colocasiomyia colocasiae (Duda) (A, lateral view; B, ventral view; C, hypandrium and gonocoxites, oblique lateral view), C. xenalocasiae (Okada) (D, lateral view; E, ventral view), C. sabahana sp. nov. (F, lateral view; G, ventral view) and C. cristata de Meijere (H, lateral view; I, ventral view).Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; goncx, gonocoxite; hypd, hypandrium; phap, phallapodeme; ph sh, phallal sheath. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766424/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Figs 11F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[475,516,1627,1653]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">24I</figureCitation>
). Epiproct and hypoproct with pubescence (ch.48-0). Oviscapt shorter than phallus (apodeme + sheath), with ovisensilla only on distal portion occupying less than 1/2 of total length (ch.49-0, 51-1). Puparium (3rd instar larva): segments with stout spicules on ventral surface; anterior spiracle with stalk ending in a whorl of 19–25 long branches; stalk as long as posterior spiracle and longer than longest branch; caudal segments not so elongate, with many small spicules, ending in a V-shaped pair of long posterior spiracles (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1424,1771,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1798,1822]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetId="figure-110@37.[179,1407,478,1774]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 24. Colocasiomyia sabahana Toda, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from the Park Headquarters area, Mt. Kinabalu, Sabah, Malaysia; C,E,G,K,M,O,Q) and C. sarawakana Toda &amp; Yafuso, sp. nov. (♂ and ♀ paratypes and puparium from Kuching, Sarawak, Malaysia; A,B,D,F,H–J,L,N,P,R). A, Proboscis (caudal view); B, thorax (dorsal view); C, D, male abdominal sternites (ventral view); E, F, female abdominal sternites (ventral view); G, H, periphallic organs (lateral view); I, J, phallic organs (I, lateral view; J, ventral view); K, L, female terminalia (lateral view); M, N, puparium (ventral habitus); O, P, mouth hook; Q, R, cephalopharyngeal skeleton. Arrowheads indicate diagnostic characters. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, C–L, Q and R, 0.5 mm in B, 1.0 mm in M and N." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5766454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5766454/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 24M,N</figureCitation>
). Mouth hook moderately, triangularly expanded medioventrally in lateral view; distal blade as long as basal portion, apically pointed, gently curved downward, with two rows of small, acute teeth on submedial to subapical portion of ventral margin (
